Wiley / Overleaf reminder

There are currently 3 manuscript-like TeX files related to the Wiley Overleaf setup:

1. overleaf_bundle/main.tex
   This looks like the main Overleaf bundle entry file and is the newest/larger bundle copy.

2. drafts/overleaf_bundle/main.tex
   This is another main.tex copy inside drafts. It is not identical to the root bundle main.tex.

3. drafts/overleaf_bundle/wileyintegration.tex
   This looks like another manuscript variant or earlier integration file.

Important:
- There are two different files named main.tex.
- That is probably why the structure feels confusing.
- The root overleaf_bundle/ folder also contains Wiley support files such as wiley-article.cls and vancouver-authoryear.bst.

Suggested organization:
- Keep overleaf_bundle/ as the final upload-ready Wiley bundle.
- Treat overleaf_bundle/main.tex as the single canonical file for Overleaf compilation.
- Keep drafts/ only for work-in-progress material.
- Rename drafts/overleaf_bundle/main.tex to something clearer like main_draft.tex.
- Rename drafts/overleaf_bundle/wileyintegration.tex to something clearer like manuscript_source.tex or integrated_review.tex.
- Add a short README in each folder saying which file should be edited and which file is only a copy/export.

Simple rule to follow:
- Edit one source file only.
- Export or copy to the final overleaf_bundle/ only when you are ready to upload.
